==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[vulnerarius]]'', from ''[[vulnus]]'' ‘wound’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈvʌlnərəri/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{obsolete}} Useful or used for [[healing]] [[wounds]]; healing, [[curative]].
#:*'''1819''': Rebecca examined the wound, and having applied to it such '''vulnerary''' remedies as her art prescribed, informed her father that [...] there was nothing to fear for his guest’s life — Walter Scott, ''Ivanhoe''
# {{archaic}} {{rare}} Causing [[wounds]], [[wounding]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|vulneraries}}

# A vulnerary [[substance]].

